name: ViaVia
accessibility: Bring anything, except maybe to much own food.
vibe: Calm music, perfect lighting, not too shady.
furniture: Standard but decent chairs and high tables.
technical: Free WiFi, VPN working, some plugs near the walls.

name: KBR
accessibility: A library is card required, and you must leave your bag in a locker with coin-mechanism. The bike parking is limited.
food: No food allowed, except in the cafetaria upstairs.
protip: You can also work in the cafétaria upstairs

name: Muntpunt
vibe: Good vibe, although it can be quite noisy. Sit with your back to the windows if you don't want to be distracted by pedestrians.
food: No food available, but shops closeby.
furniture: Sadly, the main bench has no backrest.
protip: You can rent out some books or games!

name: Belga
accessibility: Free entrance, but gets crowded when the evening nears.

name: SmartBE
accessibility: Free access, very safe. Limited bike parking.
vibe: Great working athmosphere and cosy courtyard. The bright lighting facilitates your focus.
furniture: There's a lot of space with decent tables and chairs.
technical: VPN can be problem. Ample plugs
protip: Go get a 5 euro salad at Hibiscus.

name: Boentje
vibe: Stylish interior but feels quite small and the lighting can be dim.
furniture: Not that much space, but good tables.
protip: The food is expensive but very good, so give it a try!

name: CIVA
accessibility: A library card is required (5 euro for 1 stay, 10 euro per year), and the use of lockers is required. It's located on a steep road, so you might arrive a little sweaty.
vibe: Good lighting, nice building. Can get hot in summer. Library workers can make some noise.
technical: Every table has a plug, but inconvenient placement under table.

name: Faculté d’architecture de l’ULB
accessibility: Free access. Don't be shy, visitors are welcome here!
vibe: Nice building and courtyard. People leave all kinds of stuff laying around.
furniture: Variety of tables and chairs, including some loungy soft seats.
technical: University login required, unless temporary free wifi in place.
protip: There are some nice spots on the first floor with view on the courtyard. Walk around to spot some of the maquettes!

name: Le Phare du Kanaal
protip: Terras with late sunlight. Explore the multiple levels (working spaces).

name: Coworking Kalmthout
accessibility: A test-day is possible, the membership is payed. Kalmthout is a little far, though.
vibe: There's a productive balance: it's pleasant but not to cosy.
furniture: Old meeting tables of municipality - they are chunky but do the job. Comfortable chairs, but there are some uncomfortable plastic chairs as well.
technical: Ample plugs and free WiFi. VPN is not working.
protip: Great lunch at Isa's, incl. Bas+Lou.

name: Barbican Center
vibe: Your neighbors might be a little noisy but a lot of people are working here. The lighting is a little dim. If you want to leave your stuff for a while, ask someone to keep an eye on it!
food: There's a coffee shop and a restaurant.
technical: Not a lot of plugs. VPN works.
protip: Have a walk around this landmark building. There's an extra working space in the Barbican café across the road.

name: Central Coworking @ Zetter Café
accessibility: Free access if you pretend like you belong. There's a membership system, but just mention you're on a trial visit if they ask.
vibe: Super calm, great working vibe. You don't have to order something.
food: You can order drinks, but they can be expensive.
furniture: Very nice velvet chairs, and ideal tabourret spots with lookout on the Saint John's Piory.
technical: Ample plugs and free WiFi. VPN is working.
protip: For your lunch break, head to Leather Lane!

name: PPF
vibe: You might feel a little 'alone' here, but this also means you can focus! Take a walk in the garden on your break.
food: Snacks in the cupboard above the dryer! There's a shop on the corner with Meersstraat.
furniture: Anything from century-old coaches over post-modern fauteuils to standard chairs.
technical: Ample plugs and free WiFi. VPN is working.
protip: When done working, go for a run around blaarmeersen. Running shoes and shower available!

name: Bisdom Gent
accessibility: Only Bertrand can get you in. Getting out and in again is cumbersome.
vibe: Theological productivity boost. Don't come hear of hearing footsteps on a wooden floor brings you out of focus.
food: No food available, and eating should be done discretely. You can get food in town.
protip: Ask for a tour, including the wine cellar.

name: Popup coworking Tervuren
accessibility: You can get here by tram or car, but should know someone to get inside.
vibe: Quiet, productive vibe and fun breaks. Working hours of coworkers may vary.
furniture: Desks, beds, sofa's, you name it! Multiple rooms may be available.
technical: Ample plugs and free WiFi. VPN is working.
protip: Tervuren park is closeby, go for a run after work!
